@startuml
title Input Reaches Widgets - Beginner Flow

skinparam ParticipantPadding 8

participant "Operating system" as OS
participant "Sparkle platform layer" as Platform
participant "Window event queues" as Queues
participant "Input modules" as Modules
participant "Widget tree" as Widgets

OS -> Platform : mouse, keyboard, resize, close messages
Platform -> Queues : stores Sparkle event records

... next update tick ...

Modules -> Queues : read pending events
Modules -> Modules : update Mouse / Keyboard state
Modules -> Widgets : dispatch typed events

alt widget consumes event
	Widgets --> Modules : stop propagation
else not consumed
	Widgets -> Widgets : continue through tree
end

note over OS,Widgets
The operating system is translated into Sparkle events.
Widgets see typed events such as mouse move, key press,
text input, resize, and close requested.
end note

@enduml
